This paper is primarily focused on image denoising, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of the Sinkhorn-Knopp algorithm, which is commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper uses statistical learning techniques, which are relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of various denoising algorithms, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
